<br>
First off, where did I state my opinion on the legalization of drugs? I just said that they were not victimless crimes. You can make arguments for the legalization of drugs, many of them very valid - however, drugs kill people. That is a fact, not an opinion.<br>
<br>
Wayfarer, you seem to think that drugs are a symbol of freedom, and that they only affect the people that use them. That is entirely incorrect.<br>
<br>
Fact: Some drug users steal money to pay for their addiction.<br>
<br>
Fact: Most rapes occur when the rapist is under the influence of drugs or alcohol.<br>
<br>
Fact: Most unmeditated murders occur when the murderer is under the influence of drugs or alcohol.<br>
<br>
Fact: People are killed every day as a result of drivers under the influence of drugs or alcohol. Some of those people were intoxicated at the time, others were not.<br>
<br>
I don't know about you, but I don't feel so &quot;free&quot; when someone has stolen my money or raped me, and I feel especially burdened when dead. <p><IMG SRC=http://www.tiannathomas.com/images/roliel3.gif>
