<br>
&quot;Cigarets and alcohol are highly addictive.<br>
Marihuana isn't.<br>
Cigarets and alcohol are a high danger for your body.<br>
Marihuana is in fact healthy.&quot;<br>
<br>
I thought these were highly dangerous statements. It was almost an endorsement to &quot;go out and smoke pot now! It's good for you!&quot;<br>
<br>
Nothing your body takes in that causes any sort of high is healthy. Pot is addictive, just not anywhere near the order of nicotine. I distinctly remember my roomate going through all sorts of gyrations for several days, even missing work, in order to score some weed when supplies dried up. He was a heavy user, taking frequent breaks at work to slip outside and smoke a bowl in his car. It was very reminiscent of someone smoking a couple packs of cigarettes a day, then trying to quit cold turkey. Some people can do it, others can't. <br>
<br>
Just because I was able to quit drinking easily does not mean alcohol isn't addictive. Likewise just because you were able to easily lay off the pot does not mean it isn't also addictive. Hell, caffeine in coffee, tea or soda is addictive to a certain degree.<br>
<br>
As far as pot being healthy....that depends. It has some medicinal value in chronic cases when used in moderation. It has no benefit to the casual recreational user beyond making them feel good from the high and causes long term lung damage and fertility problems to heavy smokers. Like any drug taken in excessive amount it will cause more health problems than it will solve. Moderation is the key. <p>Gulor Gularin
